{
  "texts": [
    "LLMs do this, by covering it up, excluding responses that express views offensive to liberal sensibility.",
    "Euphemistically, the LLM makers do this with \"supervised machine learning.\"",
    "A not-funny joke says that \"AI\" stands for \"Absent Indian\"-the cheap global labor-force that laboriously trains the AI not to say certain things.",
    "• Jailbreak -A clever prompt that gets past the filters (Shen et al. 2023).• Hallucination -When Generative AI makes up facts: It only knows how to write good sentences but has no way of checking whether the content is true (Klein 2023, Munn, Magee andArora 2023b).",
    "• Black Box -There is no knowing exactly which source texts have been used in response to a prompt and how the AI came to generate a particular sentence."
  ]
}